{"lemma":"فَرِحُ","slug":"فَرِحُ","root":"ف.ر.ح","root_slug":"ف-ر-ح","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ر-ح","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"فَرِح","root":"فرح","pos":"N","occurrence_count":6},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":9},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n33398","","n33400","n33401","n33402"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%90%D8%AD%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be happy, to be glad, to be merry, to be joyful, to exult, to rejoice (بِ (bi) in)","tags":["stative"],"examples":[{"text":"إِنْ تَمْسَسْكُمْ حَسَنَةٌ تَسُؤْهُمْ وَإِن تُصِبْكُمْ سَيِّئَةٌ يَفْرَحُوا بِهَا"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be pleased, to be content","tags":["stative"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of فَرِحَ (fariḥa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb","obsolete"],"examples":[{"text":"لَا تَفْرَحْ إِنَّ ٱللَّهَ لَا يُحِبُّ ٱلْفَرِحِينَ"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"happiness, gladness, mirth, joy, exultation"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a state of being well pleased or content"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"wedding"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make glad, happy"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"happy, glad, merry, joyful, exulting"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"well pleased, content"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/fa.ri.ħa/","/fa.raħ/","/far.ra.ħa/","/fa.riħ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n33398","headword_ar":"فَرِحَ","root":"frH","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, L, Msb, K, &c.,) [aor."},{"kind":"text","text":",] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraHN","text_ar":"فَرَحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, * L, * Msb, &c.,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He rejoiced; was joyful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"glad;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was happy;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, L, Msb, K, &c.;) syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sur~a","text_ar":"سُرَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, A, Msb, * &c.:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he experienced a sensation of lightness in his heart:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Th, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his bosom became dilated with delight,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pleasure, of short continuance, transitory,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fleeting, not lasting, as is the case in bodily and worldly pleasures;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraHN","text_ar":"فَرَحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"differing from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suruwrN","text_ar":"سُرُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the manner expl. below, though each is sometimes used as syn. with the other. (Er-Rághib, TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fariHa bihi","text_ar":"فَرِحَ بِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He rejoiced, was joyful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"glad,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was happy, by reason of him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sur~a","text_ar":"سُرَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, A, Msb. *) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, well pleased,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"content."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He exulted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rejoiced above measure;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he exulted greatly, and behaved insolently and unthankfully,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ungratefully."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K.) The verb is used in this sense in the Kur xxviii. 76. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Th","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n33400","headword_ar":"فَرَحٌ","root":"frH","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fariHa","text_ar":"فَرِحَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.: as a simple subst.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Joy, mirth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gladness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"happiness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, Msb, K;) syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suruwrN","text_ar":"سُرُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuzonN","text_ar":"حُزْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taraHN","text_ar":"تَرَحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S and A in art"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"trH","text_ar":"ترح"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sensation of lightness of the heart:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Th, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dilatation of the bosom with delight,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pleasure, of short continuance, transitory,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fleeting, not lasting, as is the case in bodily and worldly pleasures;"},{"kind":"text","text":"whereas"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suruwrN","text_ar":"سُرُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is dilatation of the bosom with delight, or pleasure, wherein is quiet or tranquillity or rest of mind, of short or of long continuance; but each is sometimes used as syn. with the other. (Er-Rághib, TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A state of being well pleased,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"content,"},{"kind":"text","text":"with a thing. (Msb.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Exultation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a rejoicing above measure;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a state of exulting greatly, and behaving insolently and unthankfully,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ungratefully."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K.) ―         -b4-  [Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A festivity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"merry-making;"},{"kind":"text","text":"particularly, as used in the present day,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on the occasion of a marriage."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b5-  Pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aforaAHN","text_ar":"اَفْرَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b6-  In the saying of Muteea Ibn-Iyás,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"qado Zafira AlHuzonu biAls~uruwri waqado\n                      \n                     \n                        A^udiyla makoruwhunaA mina AlfaraHi"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sorrow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sadness, has overcome happiness, and the object of our dislike,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hatred, has been given a turn to prevail over the object of our love"},{"kind":"text","text":"], by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mina AlfaraHi","text_ar":"مِنَ الفَرَحِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"he means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mina AlmaforuwHi bihi","text_ar":"مِنَ المَفْرُوحِ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaHobuwbi","text_ar":"المَحْبُوبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Ham p. 391.)"}],"source_refs":["L","Th","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n33401","headword_ar":"فَرُحٌ","root":"frH","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the paragraph here following."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n33402","headword_ar":"فَرِحٌ","root":"frH","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faroHaAnu","text_ar":"فَرْحَانُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faruHN","text_ar":"فَرُحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in some copies of the K and in the L and other lexicons, or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faruwHN","text_ar":"فَرُوحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in other copies and mentioned by IJ, (TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAriHN","text_ar":"فَارِحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maforuwHN","text_ar":"مَفْرُوحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) the last mentioned by IJ; (TA;) fem. [of the first]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fariHapN","text_ar":"فَرِحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [of the second]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faroHaY","text_ar":"فَرْحَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faroHaAnapN","text_ar":"فَرْحَانَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) but of the correctness of this last ISd was not certain: (TA:) pl. [of the first]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fariHuwna","text_ar":"فَرِحُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb) and [of the second]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraAHaY","text_ar":"فَرَاحَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faroHaY","text_ar":"فَرْحَى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Rejoicing, joyful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"glad;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"happy:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K:) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"experiencing a sensation of lightness in the heart:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having the bosom dilated with delight,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pleasure, of short continuance, transitory,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fleeting, not lasting, as is the case in bodily and worldly pleasures."},{"kind":"text","text":"See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraHN","text_ar":"فَرَحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] Hence, in the Kur [iii. 164],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fariHiyna bimaA A=taAhumu","text_ar":"فَرِحِينَ بِمَا ا=تَاهُمُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@ll~`hu mino faDolihi","text_ar":"ا@للّٰهُ مِنْ فَضْلِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Rejoicing by reason of that which God has given them of his bounty"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Well pleased,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"content:"},{"kind":"text","text":"whence, in the Kur [xxiii. 55 and xxx. 31],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kul~u HizobK bimaA ladayohimo fariHuwna","text_ar":"كُلُّ حِزْبٍ بِمَا لَدَيْهِمْ فَرِحُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Every sect is well pleased,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"content, with that"},{"kind":"text","text":"religion"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which it has"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Exulting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rejoicing above measure;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exulting greatly, and behaving insolently and unthankfully,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ungratefully:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K:) whence, in the Kur [xxviii. 76],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a A@ll~`ha laA yuHib~u AlfariHiyna","text_ar":"اـِنَّ ا@للّٰهَ لَا يُحِبُّ الفَرِحِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily God does not love those who exult,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rejoice above measure;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (S, Msb.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","K","TA","S"]}]}}